description.narrative: The development objectives are to: (a) accelerate, in a commercially viable manner, the use of electricity for economic growth and social services and thus improve the quality of life in un-served and underserved areas (peri-urban and rural); (b) improve governance and ensure the financial sustainability of the sector, through the involvement of the private sector in partnership with the public sector; (c) reduce deforestation and increase access and diversify choice to renewable and cleaner fuels to the household and SME sectors; and (d) promote regional cooperation while protecting the environment in a sustainable manner.

title.narrative: Accelerate, in a commercially viable manner, the use of electricity in underserved areas for economic growth and improved quality of life.

baseline.value: Limited power availability in northern Benin through diesel-fired powerplant at Parakou and Djougou, which is often not able tooperate due tolack of diesel. 0 GWh supplied from southern grid.

target.value: Reliable power supplied to northern Benin through the interconnected grid as measured in GWh supplied from southern grid.

actual.value: Reliable and cheaper electricity is used in northern Benin

title.narrative: Forestry and Ecology Information System (SIEF) and Energy Sector Information and Monitoring System (SIEP) operational.

baseline.value: No comprehensive forestry or energy sector information system available.

target.value: SIEF and SIEP are completed and fully operational.

actual.value: SIEF and SIEF are completed and operational

title.narrative: Improve governance of the biomass energy sub-sector and strengthen the relevant institutions.

target.value: Establ. and effective functioning of the the Nat. Household Energy Commission (CNCD) and the Inter-com. Agency for Nat. ResourceManagement (AFIC). Effective devolution of nat. resources management.

actual.value: CNCD and AFIC are established and functioning

baseline.value: No power provided to northern Benin through the Togolese power grid.

target.value: Power provided to northern Benin through the Togolese power grid, as measured in GWh supplied.

actual.value: Power is provided to nothern Benin from northern Togo

title.narrative: Feasibility and EIA/RAP Studies for the transmission lines of Onigbolo-Parakou and Sakete-Porto Novo completed.
Strengthen the capacity of Benin to expand the power sector.

baseline.value: SBEE fully publicly owned and low financial and technical performance. No studies available to expand the electricity system. Nostrategy or policy for off-grid electrification.

target.value: Strategy for off-grid electrification developed and endorsed. SBEE outsources key areas and financial and technical performanceimproved. Higher reliability of power supply in Cotonou and Porto Novo.

actual.value: SBEE financial situation continue to improve
